28/11/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia and Montenegro -- Macedonian Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and Macedonian Army General Staff Chief General Metodi Stamboliski visited Kosovo on Thursday (27 November). 
The Macedonian delegation held meetings with UNMIK head Harri Holkeri, Kosovo Prime Minister Bajram Rexhepi and KFOR Commander Lieutenant General Holger Kammerhoff. 
Talks focused on regional security concerns and on organised crime and corruption. 
Buckovski said Macedonia would respect any solution for the problem of Kosovo's status that does not jeopardise its sovereignty and territorial integrity. 
(Utrniski Vesnik, Dnevnik - 28/11/03; MIA - 27/11/03)
